<sn><md>### Effects of Gibberellins

* Cell elongation
* GA induces `cellular division and cellular elongation`;<br> auxin induces `cellular elongation alone`
* GA-stimulated elongation does not involve the `cell wall acidification characteristic` of auxin-induced elongation
* Breaking of `dormancy` in buds and seeds
* `Seed germination` — especially in cereal grasses like barley; not necessarily as critical in dicot seeds
* Promotion of flowering
* Increase fruit size

:::.note
#### Fruit Formation : <br>
"Thompson Seedless" grapes grown in California are treated with GA to increase size and decrease packing
